---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Kitchen Renovations Gungahlin | Newer Homes &amp; Upgrades"
  description="Kitchen renovations in Gungahlin — upgrading builder-grade kitchens with custom cabinetry, stone benchtops and butler's pantries across Canberra's newer north. ACT-licensed. Free measure &amp; quote."
  canonical="https://kitchenrenovationscanberra.com.au/gungahlin/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Gungahlin &middot; Harrison &middot; Casey &middot; Ngunnawal &middot; Amaroo</span>
      <h1>Kitchen renovations in <span class="accent">Gungahlin</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Gungahlin is Canberra&rsquo;s newer north &mdash; estates of project homes
        where the original builder-grade kitchen is the first thing owners want
        to upgrade. We replace them with custom cabinetry, compliant stone
        benchtops and butler&rsquo;s pantries that lift a standard home to
        something special.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Gungahlin</span>
      <h2>The Gungahlin kitchen story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Builder-grade kitchens ready for an upgrade.</h3>
        <p>
          Gungahlin grew rapidly through the 2000s and 2010s &mdash; Harrison,
          Casey, Ngunnawal, Amaroo, Forde, Bonner &mdash; with estate after estate
          of project homes. Those homes were built quickly to a price, which means
          the standard <strong>builder-grade kitchen</strong>: melamine cabinetry,
          basic benchtops, entry-level appliances. As owners settle in and budgets
          allow, that kitchen is the first thing they want to lift &mdash; and
          Gungahlin&rsquo;s strong household incomes mean people invest properly
          when they do.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">The premium upgrade Gungahlin wants.</h3>
        <p>
          The typical Gungahlin brief is an upgrade, not a rescue: replace the
          builder-grade kitchen with <a href="/services/custom-cabinetry/">custom
          cabinetry</a>, a <a href="/services/benchtops/">stone or porcelain
          benchtop</a>, integrated appliances and &mdash; nearly every time &mdash;
          a <strong>walk-in or butler&rsquo;s pantry</strong>. Because the homes
          are modern and structurally sound, these projects are often clean,
          predictable renovations focused on finish and storage rather than
          fixing underlying problems.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Modern homes, modern compliance.</h3>
        <p>
          Gungahlin homes are recent slab-on-ground builds, so there&rsquo;s no
          asbestos concern of the kind you find in older Canberra suburbs &mdash;
          but moving plumbing means cutting into a slab, so layout changes are
          planned carefully. All plumbing is done to <strong>AS/NZS 3500</strong>
          and electrical to <strong>AS/NZS 3000</strong> by ACT-licensed trades
          under the <strong>Construction Occupations (Licensing) Act 2004</strong>,
          certified at handover.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Knock-down-rebuild &amp; new-home kitchens.</h3>
        <p>
          Gungahlin also sees knock-down-rebuild and new-home activity, where
          owners want a designed kitchen rather than a project-home default from
          the start. We work to your plans (or design from scratch), coordinating
          the kitchen so it&rsquo;s ready at lock-up stage &mdash; the same
          custom cabinetry and compliant benchtops, planned in from day one.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Gungahlin kitchen jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Upgrading a builder-grade kitchen to custom cabinetry + stone benchtop ($30K&ndash;$55K)</li>
          <li>Adding a walk-in butler&rsquo;s pantry to a Harrison or Forde home</li>
          <li>Premium island kitchen with integrated appliances in Casey</li>
          <li>New-home or knock-down-rebuild kitchen built to the owner&rsquo;s design</li>
          <li>Porcelain waterfall island and full re-cabinet in an Amaroo family home</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/belconnen/">Belconnen</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/tuggeranong/">Tuggeranong</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/woden/">Woden</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/dickson/">Dickson</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/canberra-region/">All Canberra &amp; the ACT</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Gungahlin kitchen quote.</h2>
        <p>Builder-grade upgrades, butler&rsquo;s pantries, premium islands. Custom cabinetry, fixed-price quotes.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
